<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-09-28T21:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-09-28T21:00:00-05:00" n="524" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d524">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/13975: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-09-29T09:00:00+07:00">September 29, 1938—9
                                    a.m.</date><lb/>[Received September 29—8 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>570. My 469, September 28, 1 p.m.<note n="66" xml:id="d524fn66">Not
                                printed.</note> In my interview with the Minister for Foreign
                            Affairs yesterday he informed me that he had received word that League
                            had voted to apply sanctions against Japan and he again expressed the
                            hope that United States would support the League in any way within its
                            power.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>